## 2. User Roles & Access Control

### 2.1 Roles
| Role | Description |
|---|---|
| **Admin** | Manages the entire Ajo group. Full visibility into all members' data, all financial records, and all settings. Can create/edit/delete members, savings commitments, and settings. |
| **Member** | A regular saver. Can only see their own dashboard, their own savings commitments, their own submitted requests, and general notifications. Cannot see other members' financial data or admin tools. |

### 2.2 Access Rules
- Every page/tab must check the logged-in user's role server-side (not just hide UI elements) before returning data.
- **Admin Dashboard**: aggregated values across all members.
- **Member Dashboard**: values scoped to `WHERE user_id = current_user`.
- Admin-only tabs: Manage Users, Settings, Deleted Records, Waiting List, Savings Commitments Report (full), Submitted Requests (all members).
- Member-accessible tabs: Dashboard (own data), Savings Commitment (own records, read + request), Notifications (own), Submitted Requests (own only).

### 2.3 Authentication
- Email + password login, with password reset flow.
- Invitation-based onboarding (see Section 4 — Manage Users).
- Session/JWT-based auth; role stored in the token/session and re-validated per request.

