## 4. Manage Users Tab *(Admin only)*

### 4.1 Table Columns
| Column | Notes |
|---|---|
| Invitation ID | System-generated unique ID |
| Name | Full name |
| Email | Unique, used for login/invite |
| Phone Number | |
| Role | Admin / Member |
| Created On | Date record created |
| Is Active | Boolean — whether the user has activated/logged into their account |
| Membership | Membership status/type (e.g., Active, Pending, Suspended — define enum with client) |
| Action | Hamburger menu: View / Edit / Delete |

### 4.2 Search
- A search input above the table that filters by name, email, or phone number (server-side or client-side filtering, debounced).

### 4.3 Add Member Flow
- **"Add Member" button** at the top opens a modal form with fields: Name, Email, Phone Number, Role, Membership.
- Two submit actions on the form:
  1. **"Save"** — creates the member record and sends an email to both the Admin and the new member. The email is a registration/welcome notice only (no login link).
  2. **"Save and Invite"** — creates the member record and sends a welcome email to the member that **includes a unique invitation link** to access the dashboard and sign in (e.g., a tokenized URL that lets them set a password and log in). Also notifies the admin.
- Both emails should be transactional templates (see Section 12 — Notifications & Emails).

### 4.4 Row Actions (Hamburger Menu)
- **View** — read-only detail view/modal of the member's profile.
- **Edit** — opens the same form pre-filled, allows updating details.
- **Delete** — soft-delete (moves record to **Deleted Records** tab, does not hard-delete from the database) with a confirmation prompt.

