## 5. Savings Commitment Tab

### 5.1 Table Columns
| Column | Notes |
|---|---|
| Record ID | System-generated |
| Member Name | |
| Savings Amount | Committed contribution amount |
| Collection Month | Month this commitment/collection cycle applies to |
| End Date | End date of the commitment |
| Status | e.g., Pending, Payment Confirmed, Harvest Released, Cancelled — define enum with client |
| Action | Hamburger menu (see 5.5) |

### 5.2 Search & Filters
- Search input (by member name).
- **Year filter** dropdown to scope the table to a specific year.

### 5.3 "New Savings Commitment" Button → Modal Form
Form fields (all dropdowns sourced from existing system data):
| Field | Source of options |
|---|---|
| Savers * | Dropdown list of registered members (from Manage Users) |
| Savings Commitment Amount * | Dropdown from **Settings → Commitment Amount** list |
| Collection Month * | Dropdown, Jan–Dec |
| Collection Year * | Dropdown of years (e.g., current year ± a configurable range) |
| Savings Commitment Goal * | Dropdown from **Settings → Savings Commitment** goal list (Debt Repayment, Dream Holiday, Investment, My First Home, Property Purchase, Savings, School Fees, Wedding, Other) |

Two buttons on the form:
- **"Request Collection Month"** — submits the commitment and triggers a **request/notification workflow** asking the member to confirm/acknowledge the collection month (appears under Submitted Requests and Notifications).
- **"Save"** — saves the commitment directly without triggering the request workflow.

> **Open question for client:** Confirm exact difference in system behavior between "Request Collection Month" and "Save" — assumption above is that "Request" creates a pending request needing member/admin action, while "Save" commits it immediately as active.

### 5.4 "Send Reminder" Button → Modal Form
Fields:
| Field | Source |
|---|---|
| Savers * | Dropdown of members |
| Saving Commitment * | Dropdown of that member's existing savings commitments |

- **"Send"** button dispatches a reminder notification/email to the selected saver about their selected commitment (e.g., upcoming due date or unconfirmed payment).

### 5.5 Row Actions (Hamburger Menu)
- **Confirm Payment Receipt** — admin marks the offline payment as received/confirmed for that record.
- **Payment for Past Month** — allows logging/backfilling a payment against a prior month's collection cycle.
- **Release Harvest** — marks the accumulated savings as released/paid out to the member; updates "Harvest Released to Date" metric.
- **Cancel** — cancels the commitment record (should prompt confirmation; consider whether this soft-deletes to Deleted Records or just sets Status = Cancelled).

### 5.6 Member View
- Members see only their own rows in this tab (their own commitments), and can view status but cannot access admin-only actions like Confirm Payment Receipt or Release Harvest.

