## 10. Settings Tab *(Admin only)*

### 10.1 Savings Commitment Goals (Toggle List)
Admin can enable/disable which savings goals are available for selection elsewhere in the app (e.g., in the New Savings Commitment form). Each goal has an on/off toggle:
- Debt Repayment
- Dream Holiday
- Investment
- My First Home
- Property Purchase
- Savings
- School Fees
- Wedding
- Other

Only "on" goals should appear as selectable options in dropdowns throughout the app.

### 10.2 Commitment Amounts (Toggle List)
Admin can enable/disable preset commitment amount options, also each with an on/off toggle. Example seed values:
55.00, 100.00, 101.00, 120.00, 122.00, 200.00, 250.00, 300.00, 400.00, 500.00, 600.00, 700.00, 750.00, 1000.00, 1021.00, 1100.00, 2000.00, 20000.00

> Note: the original list had duplicate 400.00 and 1100.00 entries — dedupe when seeding data, but keep the ability for admin to add new custom amounts (recommend adding an "Add new amount" input alongside the toggle list rather than a fixed hardcoded set).

### 10.3 Requirements
- Only "on"/active toggled goals and amounts should populate the dropdowns in the Savings Commitment form (Section 5.3).
- Admin should be able to add new custom goals/amounts, not just toggle the seed list (recommended — confirm with client).

