## 13. Data Model (Suggested Entities)

- **User**: id, name, email, phone, role (admin/member), is_active, membership_status, created_on, invitation_token, invitation_status
- **SavingsCommitment**: id, user_id (FK), amount, goal (FK to CommitmentGoal), collection_month, collection_year, end_date, status, created_on
- **PaymentRecord**: id, savings_commitment_id (FK), amount, month_covered, confirmed_by (admin user_id), confirmed_on, status
- **HarvestRelease**: id, savings_commitment_id (FK), released_on, released_by (admin user_id), amount
- **Request**: id, savings_commitment_id (FK, nullable), user_id (FK), type (collection_month_request, etc.), status, requested_on
- **Notification**: id, user_id (FK, nullable for admin-broadcast), type, message, related_record_type, related_record_id, is_read, created_on
- **WaitingListEntry**: id, name, email, phone, monthly_commitment_interest, is_referred, referred_by, created_on
- **DeletedRecord**: id, original_table, original_record_id (or JSON snapshot), deleted_on, deleted_by
- **CommitmentGoalSetting**: id, label, is_active (toggle)
- **CommitmentAmountSetting**: id, amount, is_active (toggle)

> This is a starting schema — finalize field types, constraints, and relationships with the developer during technical design.

